description: Alcohol lowers the amount of thiamin in the body. Taking alpha-lipoic acid when there is a shortage of thiamine might cause serious health problems.
recommendation: Avoid taking alpha-lipoic acid with alcohol.
sources: The Health Professional's Guide to Dietary Supplements, Talbott & Hughes, 2007
